pst-9sw: give QuackWorks Modules/multiconnectSlotDesign.scad (the non-BOSL
Multiconnect backer) real module parameters, so a use<>-ing model can set
what upstream only exposes as file-scope Customizer variables.

Context: pst-7bs showed the BOSL2-based sibling backer
(Modules/multiconnectSlotDesignBOSL.scad) cannot survive the BOSL2 bump to
v2.0.747 — on the wasm engine it aborts or hangs in EVERY configuration,
including with both slot dimples and on-ramps disabled. This file is the
BOSL2-free master copy of the same Multiconnect backer (plain cube /
difference / linear_extrude / rotate_extrude / cylinder, zero BOSL2
references), so it is immune to that break and to any future BOSL2
attachment-API drift. cylindrical_holder_slot and ego_lb6500_blower_mount
now use it instead.

The blocker was purely API surface. multiconnectBack() took only
(backWidth, backHeight, distanceBetweenSlots); everything else — backer
thickness, slot ladder position, v1-dimple vs v2-snap retention — lived in
file-scope Customizer variables that `use <>` does not import and a model
cannot set. Three of those we genuinely need per call site:

1. backThickness — was hardcoded 6.5 in the module's let(). ego welds its
   backer into the plate face and needs 6.95 (backer_thickness + weld), and
   the thickness is @param-tunable 5.5..8 there. Promoted to a parameter,
   default 6.5, so upstream behaviour is unchanged.

   Upstream anchors the slot cut 2.35 mm in from the panel's y=0 (body-side)
   face, so merely widening the panel would deepen the slot along with it.
   The slot must stay a fixed 4.15 mm recess measured from the y=-t WALL
   face, with the extra meat added behind it — hence the matching
   `-(backThickness-6.5)` term on the slot translate. It is zero at the
   default thickness, so upstream geometry is untouched, and it keeps the
   engaging profile identical at every other thickness.

2. slotVerticalOffset — the slot ladder is placed at `backHeight-13`, which
   sits 2.85mm lower than the BOSL backer put it (that one defaults
   slotVerticalOffset=2.85, and 13-10.15-2.85 == 0). Measured on a 50x75
   backer: slot void top z=34.63 here vs 37.49 there. Both models pass 2.85
   to keep their shipped slot z-span. Default 0 preserves upstream placement.

3. connectVersion / quickRelease — retention style, threaded explicitly into
   slotTool() instead of being read from file scope, so the choice is
   per-call rather than global. Named distinctly from the file-scope
   multiConnectVersion / slotQuickRelease so neither shadows the other;
   slotTool still defaults to the globals, so the file's own top-level
   Customizer call behaves exactly as upstream. Both models pass
   "v2" / false, which is also what the file's defaults say.

No geometry changes at default arguments. Unlike the BOSL2-compat shim this
replaces, nothing here tracks a moving BOSL2 API — this file does not
reference BOSL2 at all — so it should not rot across BOSL2 bumps. Drop it if
upstream promotes these to module parameters.

